{"symbol": "RNF20", "uniprot": "Q5VTR2", "protein_name": "E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase BRE1A", "length": 975, "function": "Component of the RNF20/40 E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase complex that mediates monoubiquitination of 'Lys-120' of histone H2B (H2BK120ub1). H2BK120ub1 gives a specific tag for epigenetic transcriptional activation and is also prerequisite for histone H3 'Lys-4' and 'Lys-79' methylation (H3K4me and H3K79me, respectively). It thereby plays a central role inb histone code and gene regulation. The RNF20/40 complex forms a H2B ubiquitin ligase complex in cooperation with the E2 enzyme UBE2A or UBE2B; reports about the cooperation with UBE2E1/UBCH are contradictory. Required for transcriptional activation of Hox genes. Recruited to the MDM2 promoter, probably by being recruited by p53/TP53, and thereby acts as a transcriptional coactivator. Mediates the polyubiquitination of isoform 2 of PA2G4 in cancer cells leading to its proteasome-mediated degradation", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000155827", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.2795, "protein_drug": 0.571, "rna_drug": 0.627}, "flags": {"surface": false, "enzyme": true, "mod_aso": true, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "ASO", "winning_axis": "RNA", "quadrant": "Both viable", "best_route": "small molecule", "sm_score": "0.721", "sirna_score": "0.396", "aso_score": "0.531"}, "modality": "ASO", "structure": "data/structures/RNF20.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.874, "volume": 645.5, "residues": [87, 90, 93, 94, 97, 158, 159, 162, 163, 170, 174, 177, 178]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.622, "volume": 824.4, "residues": [94, 98, 101, 105, 120, 121, 122, 124, 125, 126, 127, 154, 157, 158, 162, 170, 173, 174, 176, 177, 180, 181]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.338, "volume": 771.5, "residues": [391, 394, 395, 398, 823, 826, 827, 830, 833, 834, 837]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/Q5VTR2"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "Al